# Touchstone is a UI library — there are no runtime env vars at the moment.
# This file exists so the pattern is in place: add a placeholder line here
# whenever the codebase begins to read from `process.env.<NAME>` (or
# `import.meta.env.<NAME>` in Storybook / Vite contexts).
#
# Convention: one line per var, value left blank, a brief `# what this is`
# above each. Real values live in a local `.env`, which is gitignored.
#
# EXAMPLE_VAR=
